<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Document xmlns="http://www.ortodokskoptik.id/BukuBacaanKoptik" Pascha="true" FixedDateDocument="true">   <ForceSeason id="Fasts ^ PaschaWeek ^ WatosDays ^ Weekend ^ JoyousSaturday ^ Saturdays ^ FuneralTune ^ SeasonOfAirAndFruits">      <Title>         <Language id="English">Revelation</Language>               <Language id="Arabic">رؤيا</Language>      </Title>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">            Seven oil lamps and seven candles are lit, and a cross is placed in the midst, to resemble Christ who walks among the seven lampstands (Rev 1).                  </Language>      </Comment>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">            Seven censers are lit.                  </Language>      </Comment>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">            The priest raises incense while the deacons chant the “Hymn of the Blessing (<span class="Coptic">Tenouwst m~V~iwt</span>)” followed by the Hymn for St. John the Beloved “The blessings (<span class="Coptic">Ere pic~mou</span>)” in the tune of “The Time Has Come (<span class="Coptic">Apinau swpi</span>)”:         </Language>      </Comment>             <Role id="People">         <InsertDocument path="include/HymnOfBlessing"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/RevelationIntro"/>      </Role>            <Role id="Priest">          <Comment>            <Language id="English">               Then the priests start reading the Holy Book of Revelation. Each time the word “incense” is mentioned, the priest offers incense.                     </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ثم تبتدئ الكهنة بقراءة سفر الرؤيا. وكل ما وصل القارئ إلى ذكر لفظة "بخور" يرفع الكاهن البخور.            </Language>         </Comment>      </Role>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 1" type="section"/>            </Role>            <Role id="People">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               When the reader mentions the churches, at the verse “He who has an ear let him hear” the deacons respond with “He who has an ear (<span class="Coptic">V/e~teouon masj</span>)” in the tune of the “Hymn of the Virtues (<span class="Coptic">}m/] c~nou]</span>)” (Chapters 2, 3)            </Language>         </Comment>      </Role>            <Section expanded="true">         <Title>            <Language id="English">Revelation 2</Language>            <Language id="Arabic">رؤيا 2</Language>         </Title>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 2:1-6"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  V/e~te ouon masj m~mof e~cwtem marefcwtem je ou pe e~te pipn#a# jw m~mof n~niekk~l/cia               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  “He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ لَهُ أُذُنٌ فَلْيَسْمَعْ مَا يَقُولُهُ الرُّوحُ لِلْكَنَائِسِ               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>                     <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  v/eyna[ro eie~] naf n~tefouwm e~bol qen pis~s/n n~te p~wnq v/etqen y~m/] m~piparadicoc n~te panou].               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  To him who overcomes I will give to eat from the tree of life, which is in the midst of the Paradise of God.”’               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ لَهُ أُذُنٌ فَلْيَسْمَعْ مَا يَقُولُهُ الرُّوحُ لِلْكَنَائِسِ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <BibleReference reference="Revelation 2:8-10"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  V/e~te ouon masj m~mof e~cwtem marefcwtem je ou pe e~te pipn#a# jw m~mof n~niekk~l/cia               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  “He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ لَهُ أُذُنٌ فَلْيَسْمَعْ مَا يَقُولُهُ الرُّوحُ لِلْكَنَائِسِ               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>            <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>                     <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  v/ gar eyna[ro n~nou[itf n~jonc n~je pimou m~mahb#.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  He who overcomes shall not be hurt by the second death.”’               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ يَغْلِبُ فَلاَ يُؤْذِيهِ الْمَوْتُ الثَّانِي».               </Language>            </Text>                        <BibleReference reference="Revelation 2:12-16"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  V/e~te ouon masj m~mof e~cwtem marefcwtem je ou pe e~te pipn#a# jw m~mof n~niekk~l/cia               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  “He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ لَهُ أُذُنٌ فَلْيَسْمَعْ مَا يَقُولُهُ الرُّوحُ لِلْكَنَائِسِ               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>                     <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  v/ gar eyna[ro eie~] naf e~bol qen pimanna eth/p ouoh eie~] naf n~oual n~ouwbs ouoh n~h~r/i qen pial e~ouon ouran m~beri c~q/out hiwtf m~pe h~li nau e~rof e~b/l e~v/etaf[itf.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  To him who overcomes I will give some of the hidden manna to eat. And I will give him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written which no one knows except him who receives it.”’               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَنْ يَغْلِبُ فَسَأُعْطِيهِ أَنْ يَأْكُلَ مِنَ الْمَنِّ الْمُخْفَى، وَأُعْطِيهِ حَصَاةً بَيْضَاءَ، وَعَلَى الْحَصَاةِ اسْمٌ جَدِيدٌ مَكْتُوبٌ لاَ يَعْرِفُهُ أَحَدٌ غَيْرُ الَّذِي يَأْخُذُ».               </Language>            </Text>                        <BibleReference reference="Revelation 2:18-29"/>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>         </Section>               <Section expanded="true">         <Title>            <Language id="English">Revelation 3</Language>            <Language id="Arabic">رؤيا 3</Language>         </Title>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 3:1-6"/>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>                     <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 3:7-13"/>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>                     <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 3:14-22"/>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/HeWhoHasAnEar"/>         </Section>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 4" type="section"/>      </Role>            <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/IncenseComment"/>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 5" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 6" type="section"/>      </Role>            <Role id="People">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               At the mentioning of the names of each tribe, the deacons respond with “From the tribe (<span class="Coptic">E~bol qen t~vul/i</span>)...” (Chapter 7)            </Language>         </Comment>            </Role>            <Section expanded="true">         <Title>            <Language id="English">Revelation 7</Language>            <Language id="Arabic">رؤيا 7</Language>         </Title>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 7:1-4"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  Ebol qen t~vul/ n~iouda i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Judah twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ يَهُوذَا اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~roub/n i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Reuben twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ رَأُوبِينَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~gad i#b# n~so.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Gad twelve thousand were sealed;               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ جَادَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>            <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/JudahSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/ReubenSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/GadSealed"/>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  E~bol qen t~vul/ n~acc/r i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Asher twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ أَشِيرَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~evyalim i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Naphtali twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ نَفْتَالِي اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~Manacc/ i#b# n~so.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Manasseh twelve thousand were sealed;               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ مَنَسَّى اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/AsherSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/NaphtaliSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/ManassehSealed"/>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  E~bol qen t~vul/ n~cumewn i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Simeon twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ شَمْعُونَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~leui i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Levi twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ لاَوِي اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~ica,ar i#b# n~so.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Issachar twelve thousand were sealed;               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ يَسَّاكَرَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/SimeonSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/LeviSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/IssacharSealed"/>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  E~bol qen t~vul/ n~zaboulwn i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Zebulun twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ زَبُولُونَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ n~Iwc/f i#b# n~so                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Joseph twelve thousand were sealed;                </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ يُوسُفَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  e~bol qen t~vul/ m~beniamin i#b# n~so etauerc~v~ragizin m~mwou.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  of the tribe of Benjamin twelve thousand were sealed.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مِنْ سِبْطِ بِنْيَامِينَ اثْنَا عَشَرَ أَلْفَ مَخْتُومٍ.               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/ZebulunSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/JosephSealed"/>         <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/BenjaminSealed"/>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 7:9-17"/>         </Role>      </Section>            <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/IncenseComment"/>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 8" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 9" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 10" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 11" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 12" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 13" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 14" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 15" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 16" type="section"/>         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 17" type="section"/>      </Role>           <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 18" type="section"/>      </Role>            <Role id="People">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               At the mentioning of the word “Alleluia,” the deacons respond with “Alleluia” (three times) as in Psalm 151 or “Blessed is He (<span class="Coptic">Eulogimenoc</span>)” (Chapter 19)            </Language>         </Comment>         </Role>            <Section expanded="true">         <Title>            <Language id="English">Revelation 19</Language>            <Language id="Arabic">رؤيا 19</Language>         </Title>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  Menenca nai aicwtem m~v~r/] n~ounis] n~q~rwou n~te oum/s efos qen t~ve eujw m~moc je All/louia               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  After these things I heard a loud voice of a great multitude in heaven, saying, “Alleluia!               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  وَبَعْدَ هَذَا سَمِعْتُ صَوْتاً عَظِيماً مِنْ جَمْعٍ كَثِيرٍ فِي السَّمَاءِ قَائِلاً: «هَلِّلُويَا!               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="People">            <InsertDocument path="include/Alleluia3"/>         </Role>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  pioujai nem piw~ou nem pitaio~ nem ]jom na Pennou] ne je nefhap hanmeym/i ne.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Salvation and glory and honor and power belong to the Lord our God!               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  الْخَلاَصُ وَالْمَجْدُ وَالْكَرَامَةُ وَالْقُدْرَةُ لِلرَّبِّ إِلَهِنَا،               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 19:2"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  Ouoh v~mah afjoc je all/ louia                </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Again they said, “Alleluia!               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  وَقَالُوا ثَانِيَةً: «هَلِّلُويَا!               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="People">            <InsertDocument path="include/Alleluia3"/>         </Role>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  ouoh pec,~remtc efe~se e~p~swi sa e~neh n~te pie~neh.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Her smoke rises up forever and ever!”               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  وَدُخَانُهَا يَصْعَدُ إِلَى أَبَدِ الآبِدِينَ».               </Language>            </Text>                        <BibleReference reference="Revelation 19:4"/>         </Role>                  <Role id="People">            <InsertDocument path="include/Alleluia3"/>         </Role>                  <Role id="Reader">            <BibleReference reference="Revelation 19:5"/>                        <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  Ouoh aicwtem m~v~r/] n~ounis] n~c~m/ n~te ounis] m~m/s nem m~v~r/] n~t~c~m/ n~oum/s m~mwou nem t~c~m/ n~te hanqarabai eujor eujw m~moc je all/ louia               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  And I heard, as it were, the voice of a great multitude, as the sound of many waters and as the sound of mighty thunderings, saying, “Alleluia!               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  وَسَمِعْتُ كَصَوْتِ جَمْعٍ كَثِيرٍ، وَكَصَوْتِ مِيَاهٍ كَثِيرَةٍ، وَكَصَوْتِ رُعُودٍ شَدِيدَةٍ قَائِلَةً: «هَلِّلُويَا!               </Language>            </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="People">            <InsertDocument path="include/Alleluia3"/>         </Role>                  <Role id="Reader">            <Text>               <Language id="CopticReading">                  aferouro n~je Po#c# v] pipantokratwr.               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  For the Lord God Omnipotent reigns!               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  فَإِنَّهُ قَدْ مَلَكَ الرَّبُّ الْإِلَهُ الْقَادِرُ عَلَى كُلِّ شَيْءٍ.               </Language>            </Text>                        <BibleReference reference="Revelation 19:7-21"/>         </Role>      </Section>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 20" type="section"/>      </Role>               <InsertDocument path="pascha/saturday/include/Revelation21"/>            <Role id="Reader">         <BibleReference reference="Revelation 22" type="section"/>      </Role>            <Role id="People">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               At the end of the reading of the Apocalypse, the deacons chant “Lord have mercy (<span class="Coptic">K#e#</span>)” three times in the great tune, while the priest anoints all the congregation with the oil of the Apocalypse.            </Language>         </Comment>      </Role>            <InsertDocument path="include/AmenLordHaveMercy3"/>   </ForceSeason></Document>